text: "Dance, Dance" is the second single from Fall Out Boy's third studio album From Under the Cork Tree. Released in 2006, the single reached #3 in the U.S., becoming their second Top 10 single. ==Track Listing== CD #1: #"Dance, Dance" - 3:00 #""It's Not a Side Effect of the Cocaine, I am Thinking It Must be Love"" - 2:11 CD #2: #"Dance, Dance" - 3:00 #"A Little Less Sixteen Candles, a Little More "Touch Me"" - 2:49 7" vinyl: #"Dance, Dance" - 3:00 #"Sugar, We're Goin Down" (Zane Lowe Session - London 2006) - 3:49 == Music Video == The video shows the band performing at a homecoming dance in a high school. The video premiered in October 2006. == Chronology == *2005 - Sugar, We're Goin Down *2006 - Dance Dance *2006 - A Little Less Sixteen Candles... ==Awards== *The video won Viewer's Choice Award at the 2006 MTV Video Music Awards. ==References== Category:Fall Out Boy songs Category:2005 songs
title: Dance, Dance (Fall Out Boy song)
